		"description": "<p>You have begun the process of stitching together your magical studies and the powers from your pact in earnest. You gain the following benefits:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>You gain proficiency with the Arcana skill or an expertise die if you are already proficient.</li>\n<li>You also choose two skill specialties for Arcana of your choice. They do not count against your skill specialties known.</li>\n<li>You gain proficiency with Charisma saving throws.</li>\n<li>If you fail an Intelligence ability check, you can spend a spell point to reroll it, potentially turning a failure into a success. You can only use this benefit once per check. Once you have used this benefit a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, you can&rsquo;t do so again until you finish a short or long rest.</li>\n<li>Half your warlock levels count as wizard levels for the purpose of the @UUID[Compendium.a5e.a5e-class-features.Item.iojeid79x6ghgcw9]{Signature Spells} feature, and you can also cast a first-level signature spell for a cost of 1 spell point.</li>\n</ul>",
